'''Chirag''' (pronounced "tʃerɒɣ") is a common given name among many [[Asia]]n and [[Pacific Ocean|Pacific]] persons.

In [[Hindi]], ''Chirag'' means 'candle flame.' Chirag can also mean the hope from a candle's glow, changing its meaning to mix with more modern philosophical ideas.

This name is chosen by class [[Indian]] families. It is often used in poetry.